ğŸ§  Mental Model

Think of:

var â†’ old, problematic, avoid in modern JS

let â†’ use when value changes

const â†’ default choice (most used)

ğŸ‘‰ As a professional developer:
Use const by default. Use let only when necessary. Never use var.

ğŸ”¥ 2. var (The Dangerous One)
âš  Function Scoped (Not Block Scoped)
if (true) {
  var x = 10;
}
console.log(x); // 10 ğŸ˜±


Because var ignores block {} and only cares about functions.

âš  Redeclaration Allowed
var a = 5;
var a = 10; // No error


This can silently break large applications.

âš  Hoisting Behavior
console.log(a); // undefined
var a = 5;


Internally JS sees:

var a;
console.log(a);
a = 5;


This causes many bugs.

ğŸš€ 3. let (Modern & Safe)
âœ… Block Scoped
