  let x = 10;
}
console.log(x); // âŒ ReferenceError


Much safer and predictable.

âŒ No Redeclaration
let a = 10;
let a = 20; // âŒ Error


Prevents accidental mistakes.

âš  Temporal Dead Zone (TDZ)
console.log(a); // âŒ ReferenceError
let a = 5;


Unlike var, it doesnâ€™t give undefined.
It throws an error â†’ safer behavior.

ğŸ† 4. const (Best Practice Default)
â— Must Be Initialized
