Because:

const protects the reference

Not the internal content

ğŸ§  Think:
const = pointer cannot move
NOT = value is frozen

If you want full immutability:

Object.freeze(obj);

ğŸ’¡ Pro Developer Tips
1ï¸âƒ£ Always Start With const
